    <summary>High-performance Model Context Protocol server for PostgreSQL</summary>
    <description>mcp-postgres is a high-performance Model Context Protocol (MCP) server implementation for PostgreSQL. It provides 25+ tools for querying, analyzing, and managing PostgreSQL databases.

## Features
- **25+ PostgreSQL Tools** - Query execution, schema analysis, connection management
- **High Performance** - P95 latency &lt; 10ms, 17K+ req/sec throughput
- **MCP Compliant** - Full Model Context Protocol v1.0 support
- **Multiple Transports** - TCP, HTTP/2, stdio support
- **Connection Pooling** - Configurable connection pools with automatic recycling

## Installation
After installing via Chocolatey, use:
```
mcp-postgres --database-url "postgres://user:password@localhost:5432/dbname"
```

For more information, visit: https://github.com/corporatepiyush/mcp-pg-rust
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/corporatepiyush/mcp-pg-rust/releases/tag/v1.3.1</releaseNotes>
